track_notes: I drove up and down the road and around the triangle of roads around Stoke Knapp before parking on part grass - part road on the fairly busy B3162. It may be better parking in Broadwindsor and considering a different route... Lovely walk though and a lovely summit owned by the NT which was my last climbed of the 176 English Marilyns.

Parked outside Buck's Head cottage. West up Combe Lane and right onto bridleway. Don't miss turn to left, almost immediately, up steps. [If you come to a field gate with combination lock you missed the turn!] Continue through woods (squelchy in places) to lovely clearing at summit.

Total time (including ops): 1h 5m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T1. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
track_title: Lewesdon Hill Linear from Bucks Head. Feb 2024.
